==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harmoniphon
<hw>Har*mon"i*phon</hw> <pr>(h⟦aum⟧r*m⟦ocr⟧n"⟦icr⟧*f⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>"armoni`a</grk> harmony + <grk>fwnh`</grk>
sound.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>An obsolete wind instrument with a
keyboard, in which the sound, which resembled the oboe, was produced by
the vibration of thin metallic plates, acted upon by blowing through a
tube.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harmonist</ent>⟦br⟧
